                      YAZH-UNITY: ARCHITECTURE AUDIT
                      VAJRA — Tech Lead, Rotation 25
                      Date: 2026-06-17
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
─────────────────────
YAZH-UNITY is a Unity 6 LTS XR pet game for kids (ages 6-14, Tamil-first,
on-device AI). The project has a solid foundation: 5 commits, ~1,611 lines
of C# across 3 scripts, 3 ONNX model variants deployed (FP32/INT8/INT4),
and a tokenizer. This audit documents what exists, what's missing, and the
risks that must be addressed before Week 1 vertical slice.

2. WHAT EXISTS (VERIFIED)
──────────────────────────

  2.1 Repository
  ├── 5 commits on main (Zorba local, no remote push)
  ├── .gitignore present
  └── Clean commit history, descriptive messages

  2.2 C# Scripts (1,611 total lines)
  ├── Assets/Scripts/Core/GameManager.cs (428 lines)
  │   ├── GameState enum (7 states: MainMenu, PetSelection, BiomeActive,
  │   │   PetChat, Paused, GameOver, Settings)
  │   ├── Singleton pattern with DontDestroyOnLoad
  │   ├── Pet class (stats: Health, Energy, Hunger, Happiness)
  │   ├── PetPersonality enum (Curious, Thoughtful, Wise, Playful)
  │   ├── BiomeController (AR plane integration, resource spawning)
  │   ├── WeatherSystem (4 conditions, stat modifiers)
  │   ├── Resource/ResourceType (Water, Food, Shelter, Herb)
  │   └── 7-day survival loop with EndDay/CompleteChallenge
  │
  ├── Assets/Scripts/AI/YazhInferenceManager.cs (315 lines)
  │   ├── ONNX model loader (StreamingAssets/MLModels/)
  │   ├── Barracuda IWorker initialization (ComputePrecompiled)
  │   ├── YazhTokenizer (Tamil Unicode U+0B80-0BFF, 30K vocab)
  │   ├── Inference pipeline (tokenize → tensor → execute → sample → decode)
  │   ├── Performance profiling (latency tracking)
  │   └── Callback-based response handling
  │
  └── Assets/Scripts/AR/ARSetup.cs (129 lines)
      ├── AR session lifecycle management
      ├── Platform detection (iOS ARKit / Android ARCore)
      ├── Plane detection (horizontal/vertical/both)
      ├── Light estimation (ambient intensity)
      ├── Human segmentation occlusion (CPU)
      └── ARSessionState monitoring

  2.3 ML Models Deployed (StreamingAssets/MLModels/)
  ├── yazh-30k.onnx       (10 MB, FP32)
  ├── yazh-30k-int8.onnx  (5.0 MB, INT8 quantized)
  ├── yazh-30k-int4.onnx  (2.5 MB, INT4 quantized)
  └── yazh-tokenizer.json (220 bytes)

  2.4 Build & Config
  ├── build-yazh.sh (iOS/Android build script)
  ├── ProjectSettings.json (engine config)
  ├── README.md, DEPLOY.md, COMPLETION_SUMMARY.md, CHECKLIST.md
  └── .gitignore

3. WHAT IS MISSING
───────────────────

  3.1 CRITICAL (Blocks vertical slice)
  ├── ❌ No Unity scenes (MainMenu.unity, PetSelection.unity, BiomeArena.unity)
  │   → GameManager references scene transitions but scenes don't exist
  ├── ❌ No BuildScript class (build-yazh.sh calls BuildScript.BuildiOS/BuildAndroid)
  │   → Build script will fail at runtime
  ├── ❌ No ResourceManager class (GameManager declares it, never defined)
  │   → Compilation error
  ├── ❌ No ARLightEstimationManager in ARSetup.cs
  │   → Uses undefined type; ARFoundation has ARCameraManager for light estimation
  ├── ❌ ARSetup defines local enums (DetectionMode, LightEstimationMode,
  │   OcclusionPreferenceMode) that shadow AR Foundation's built-in enums
  │   → Compilation errors on real Unity project
  └── ❌ No asmdef files (Assembly Definition files for compilation boundaries)
      → All scripts in default assembly; no modular compilation

  3.2 HIGH (Blocks Week 2-4 milestones)
  ├── ❌ No UI scripts (dialogue HUD, pet status display, settings)
  ├── ❌ No audio manager (TTS integration, ambient soundscapes)
  ├── ❌ No save/load system (PlayerPrefs or JSON serialization)
  ├── ❌ No input manager (touch/gesture for AR interaction)
  ├── ❌ No animation controller (Mecanim state machine for pets)
  ├── ❌ No 3D models or prefabs (all empty directories)
  ├── ❌ No Tamil font assets (required for Tamil UI rendering)
  └── ❌ No STT (Speech-to-Text) integration for voice input

  3.3 MEDIUM (Blocks Week 5-8 expansion)
  ├── ❌ No achievement system
  ├── ❌ No analytics/telemetry (session tracking beyond Debug.Log)
  ├── ❌ No localization framework (Tamil + English fallback)
  ├── ❌ No NPC system
  ├── ❌ No dialogue tree system (hardcoded responses only)
  └── ❌ No biome-specific resource tables (only SangamKaadu implemented)

  3.4 LOW (Polish & ship)
  ├── ❌ No unit tests (EditMode or PlayMode)
  ├── ❌ No performance profiling markers (Unity Profiler integration)
  ├── ❌ No CI/CD pipeline (no automated builds)
  ├── ❌ No code style enforcement (.editorconfig, dotnet format)
  └── ❌ No dependency management manifest (packages/manifest.json missing)

4. ARCHITECTURE RISKS
──────────────────────

  RISK 1: Barracuda ONNX Compatibility [HIGH]
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  Issue: Barracuda has limited operator support. The Yazh 30K model may use
  ops not supported by Barracuda (e.g., certain attention patterns, custom
  layers). No validation has been done.
  Mitigation: Test model loading on target device immediately. Have a
  fallback plan (e.g., Unity Sentis, which supersedes Barracuda in newer
  Unity versions).

  RISK 2: Model Size vs. Mobile Memory [HIGH]
  ────────────────────────────────────────────
  Issue: Even INT4 model is 2.5MB. FP32 is 10MB. Mobile devices (especially
  older Android phones in target market) may have memory pressure.
  Mitigation: Use INT4 for production. Profile memory on target devices.
  Consider model streaming from device storage rather than bundling.

  RISK 3: Inference Latency on Mobile CPU [HIGH]
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────
  Issue: Target is <150ms. Barracuda ComputePrecompiled on mobile CPU may
  not achieve this for a 30K-parameter model. No benchmarking done yet.
  Mitigation: Benchmark on actual hardware. Consider GPU worker if available.
  Reduce context length or model size if needed.

  RISK 4: AR Foundation Version Compatibility [MEDIUM]
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Issue: ARSetup.cs defines local enums that shadow AR Foundation enums.
  This will cause compilation errors in a real Unity project.
  Mitigation: Remove local enums, use UnityEngine.XR.ARFoundation enums
  directly. Test with actual AR Foundation package installed.

  RISK 5: Singleton Pattern Without Thread Safety [MEDIUM]
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Issue: GameManager and YazhInferenceManager both use singleton pattern
  but don't handle edge cases (multiple instances, scene reloads).
  Mitigation: Add proper null checks. Consider ScriptableObject-based
  service locator for testability.

  RISK 6: No Error Recovery in Inference Pipeline [MEDIUM]
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Issue: If model loading fails, the app has no graceful degradation.
  Children will see a broken experience.
  Mitigation: Add fallback responses (pre-cached Tamil phrases). Show
  friendly error message in Tamil.

  RISK 7: Missing BuildScript Class [CRITICAL]
  ────────────────────────────────────────────
  Issue: build-yazh.sh references BuildScript.BuildiOS and
  BuildScript.BuildAndroid, but no BuildScript.cs exists.
  Mitigation: Create BuildScript.cs in Assets/Scripts/Core/ or
  Assets/Editor/ with static build methods.

  RISK 8: No CI/CD Pipeline [MEDIUM]
  ──────────────────────────────────
  Issue: No automated builds, tests, or deployment. All builds are manual.
  Mitigation: Set up GitHub Actions or local build automation (this task).

5. CODE QUALITY OBSERVATIONS
─────────────────────────────

  Strengths:
  + Clean singleton implementation with proper cleanup
  + Good separation of concerns (Core, AI, AR)
  + Comprehensive logging throughout
  + Tamil-first design (Unicode range, tokenizer, UI strings)
  + Performance profiling built into inference pipeline
  + Weather system has gameplay impact (not just visual)

  Weaknesses:
  - No XML documentation on public APIs (only summary blocks)
  - No interface abstractions (everything is concrete classes)
  - No dependency injection (hard to unit test)
  - Magic numbers everywhere (stat decay rates, weather cycle time)
  - No constants file for configuration values
  - BiomeController only implements SangamKaadu (other biomes are TODO)
  - Tokenizer is character-level, not true BPE (quality concern)
  - Inference uses greedy decoding (no sampling diversity)

6. RECOMMENDATIONS (PRIORITIZED)
─────────────────────────────────

  P0 — Do This Week:
  1. Create BuildScript.cs (unblock build pipeline)
  2. Fix ARSetup.cs enum conflicts (use AR Foundation enums)
  3. Create placeholder scenes (MainMenu, PetSelection, BiomeArena)
  4. Define ResourceManager class (fix compilation error)
  5. Set up CI/CD (GitHub Actions or local automation)

  P1 — Do Before Week 2:
  6. Add asmdef files for compilation boundaries
  7. Create configuration constants file
  8. Implement save/load system (JSON-based)
  9. Add Tamil font asset (Noto Sans Tamil or similar)
  10. Create UI manager stub

  P2 — Do Before Week 5:
  11. Implement proper BPE tokenizer
  12. Add top-k / nucleus sampling to inference
  13. Create dialogue tree system
  14. Add analytics/telemetry
  15. Write unit tests for GameManager state machine

7. CONCLUSION
──────────────
The YAZH-UNITY foundation is solid for a 5-commit prototype. The core
architecture (GameManager state machine, Barracuda inference, AR setup)
is well-structured and demonstrates good separation of concerns. The
critical gaps are: missing Unity scenes, missing BuildScript class, enum
conflicts in ARSetup, and no CI/CD pipeline. These are all fixable within
the current sprint. The highest technical risk is Barracuda model
compatibility — this must be validated on actual hardware immediately.

  Overall Architecture Score: 6.5/10
  ├── Code Quality:     7/10
  ├── Completeness:     4/10
  ├── Documentation:    9/10
  ├── Build Pipeline:   3/10
  └── Test Coverage:    0/10

